# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Fireball — X damage kills a creature (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-505 closed Fireball as WORKING but carried NO scripted puzzle
# with semantic assertions. The pre-existing fireball_divide_two_targets.pzl is
# a golden-log-only puzzle with no [assertions]. This audit puzzle SCRIPTS a
# single-target X-cost cast and asserts the lethal-damage outcome.
#
# Fireball is a {X}{R} sorcery: "Fireball deals X damage divided evenly, rounded
# down, among any number of targets." (A:SP$ DealDamage | NumDmg$ X | ValidTgts$
# Any; SVar:X:Count$xPaid). With a single target, all X damage hits it (CR
# 601.2b X locked from mana paid). Here P0 has 4 Mountains, so {X}{R} funds X=3,
# enough to kill a 2/2 Grizzly Bears (lethal damage -> creature dies, CR 704.5g).
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-505):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {X}{R} sorcery (spell cast assertion).
#   2. X funded from mana paid: 4 Mountains -> {3}{R} -> X=3.
#   3. Single-target DealDamage applies all X=3 to the chosen creature; 3 >= the
#      Bears' 2 toughness, so it is destroyed by lethal damage and moves to its
#      owner's graveyard (creature died event + graveyard membership).
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Fireball in hand, 4 Mountains (funds X=3 + {R}).
#   - P1: a Grizzly Bears (2/2) it controls.
#   - Script: P0 casts Fireball at the Grizzly Bears; 3 damage kills it.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Fireball Burns a Creature
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Fireball ({X}{R} sorcery) at P1's 2/2 Grizzly Bears with 4 Mountains (X=3). The 3 damage is lethal; the Bears dies into P1's graveyard. Backs issue mtg-505 (SP$ DealDamage NumDmg$ X over Count$xPaid; CR 704.5g).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Fireball
p0battlefield=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain
p0library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

[p0_script]
# Cast Fireball at P1's Grizzly Bears (the only creature on board). With 4
# Mountains the engine pays {3}{R} (X=3), dealing 3 lethal damage. Then PASS.
cast Fireball targeting Grizzly Bears
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[p1_script]
# P1 takes no proactive action.
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[assertions]
# The burn sorcery was actually cast.
spell cast Fireball
# X=3 damage was lethal to the 2/2: it died (event record — durable).
creature died Grizzly Bears
# The destroyed creature rests in its owner's (P1's) graveyard (a dead creature
# stays dead — durable end-state).
opponent graveyard contains Grizzly Bears
# Fireball itself is in P0's graveyard after resolving (sorcery -> GY).
graveyard contains Fireball
